(91, 4, '2022-05-10 10:30:05', '2022-05-10 10:30:05', '<!-- wp:image {\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"image/jpeg;base64,\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cattle are large domesticated bovines. They are most widespread species of the genus Bos. Adult females are referred to as cows and adult males are referred to as bulls. Cattle are commonly raised as livestock for meat, for milk, and for hides, which are used to make leather</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Eid Hatbazar', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'eid-hatbazar', '', '', '2022-05-10 10:30:05', '2022-05-10 10:30:05', '', 0, 'http://192.168.54.15/r49/WP/haatbazzar/?p=91', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(92, 8, '2022-05-10 10:27:31', '2022-05-10 10:27:31', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Goats are among the earliest animals domesticated by humans.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goat#cite_note-OKstate-6\">[6]</a></sup>&nbsp;The most recent genetic analysis<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goat#cite_note-Naderi_et_al._17659%E2%80%9317664-7\">[7]</a></sup>&nbsp;confirms the archaeological evidence that the wild&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bezoar_ibex\">bezoar ibex</a>&nbsp;of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zagros_Mountains\">Zagros Mountains</a>&nbsp;is the likely original ancestor of probably all domestic goats today.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goat#cite_note-OKstate-6\">[6]</a></sup></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neolithic\">Neolithic</a>&nbsp;farmers began to herd wild goats primarily for easy access to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milk\">milk</a>&nbsp;and meat, as well as to their dung, which was used as fuel; and their bones, hair, and sinew were used for clothing, building, and tools.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goat#cite_note-hadog-1\">[1]</a></sup>&nbsp;The earliest remnants of domesticated goats dating 10,000 years&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Before_Present\">Before Present</a>&nbsp;are found in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ganj_Dareh\">Ganj Dareh</a>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran\">Iran</a>.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goat#cite_note-8\">[8]</a></sup>&nbsp;Goat remains have been found at archaeological sites in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jericho\">Jericho</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Choga_Mami\">Choga Mami</a>,<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goat#cite_note-9\">[9]</a></sup>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Djeitun\">Djeitun</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%87ay%C3%B6n%C3%BC\">Çayönü</a>, dating the domestication of goats in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_Asia\">Western Asia</a>&nbsp;at between 8,000 and 9,000 years ago.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goat#cite_note-OKstate-6\">[6]</a></sup></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Studies of DNA evidence suggests 10,000 years ago as the domestication date.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goat#cite_note-Naderi_et_al._17659%E2%80%9317664-7\">[7]</a></sup></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Historically, goat hide has been used for water and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wine\">wine</a>&nbsp;bottles in both traveling and transporting wine for sale. It has also been used to produce&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parchment\">parchment</a>.<sup>[<em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\">citation needed</a></em>]</sup></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'GOAT', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'goat', '', '', '2022-05-10 10:27:31', '2022-05-10 10:27:31', '', 0, 'http://192.168.54.15/r49/WP/haatbazzar/?p=92', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(93, 5, '2022-05-10 10:29:38', '2022-05-10 10:29:38', '<!-- wp:image {\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.google.com/url?sa=i&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wikiwand.com%2Fen%2FChamois_Coloured_goat&amp;psig=AOvVaw3PBPViT7nCq7Ir_zI87iDF&amp;ust=1652264487280000&amp;source=images&amp;cd=vfe&amp;ved=0CAkQjRxqFwoTCLCRmIHb1PcCFQAAAAAdAAAAABAO\" alt=\"\"/><figcaption>Contrary to popular belief, Lorem Ipsum is not simply random text. It has roots in a piece of classical Latin literature from 45 BC, making it over 2000 years old. Richard McClintock, a Latin professor at Hampden-Sydney College in Virginia, looked up one of the more obscure Latin words, consectetur, from a Lorem Ipsum passage, and going through the cites of the word in classical literature, discovered the undoubtable source. Lorem Ipsum comes from sections 1.10.32 and 1.10.33 of \"de Finibus Bonorum et Malorum\" (The Extremes of Good and Evil) by Cicero, written in 45 BC. This book is a treatise on the theory of ethics, very popular during the Renaissance. The first line of Lorem Ipsum, \"Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet..\", comes from a line in section 1.10.32.<br></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Beautiful Goat in Bangladesh', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beautiful-goat-in-bangladesh', '', '', '2022-05-10 10:29:38', '2022-05-10 10:29:38', '', 0, 'http://192.168.54.15/r49/WP/haatbazzar/?p=93', 0, 'post', '', 0);
